clean_pf_categories <- clean_pf %>%
  mutate(Education = case_when(EDUC == 7 ~ "1st Year of College",
                               EDUC == 8 ~ "2nd Year of College",
                               EDUC == 9 ~ "3rd Year of College",
                               EDUC == 10 ~ "4th Year of College",
                               EDUC == 11 ~ "5th Year of College")) %>%
  mutate(Marital_Status = case_when(MARST == 1 | MARST == 2 ~ "Married",
                               MARST == 3 | MARST == 4 ~ "Divorced",
                               MARST == 5 ~ "Single",
                               MARST == "NA" ~ "Other"))

one hot encoding FOR marital status

encoded_data_marital_status <- clean_pf_categories  %>%
  mutate(Married  = case_when(MARST == 1 | MARST == 2 ~ "1",
                               MARST != 1 | MARST != 2 ~ "0")) %>%
  mutate(Single  = case_when(MARST == 5 ~ "1",
                             MARST != 5 ~ "0")) %>%
  mutate(Divorced  = case_when(MARST == 3 | MARST == 4 ~ "1",
                             MARST != 3 | MARST != 4 ~ "0"))
encoded_data_marital_status2 <- encoded_data_marital_status

encoded_data_marital_status2 <- clean_pf_categories  %>%
  mutate(Marital_Status = case_when(MARST == 1 | MARST == 2 ~ "Married",
                             MARST == 3 | MARST == 4 ~ "Divorced",
                             MARST == 5 ~ "Single",
                             MARST == "NA" ~ "Other")) %>%
  mutate(OWNERSHP_Rented  = case_when(OWNERSHP == 2  ~ "1",
                               OWNERSHP != 2  ~ "0")) %>%
  mutate(OWNERSHP_Owned  = case_when(OWNERSHP == 1 ~ "1",
                             OWNERSHP != 1 ~ "0")) %>%
  mutate(Fixed_Ownership  = case_when(OWNERSHP == 1 ~ "0", #so 0 means it's owned 
                             OWNERSHP == 2 ~ "1")) %>% #so 1 means it's rented %>%
  mutate(Married  = case_when(MARST == 1 | MARST == 2 ~ "1",
                               MARST != 1 | MARST != 2 ~ "0")) %>%
  mutate(Single  = case_when(MARST == 5 ~ "1",
                             MARST != 5 ~ "0")) %>%
  mutate(Divorced  = case_when(MARST == 3 | MARST == 4 ~ "1",
                             MARST != 3 | MARST != 4 ~ "0")) #%>%
final_data <- encoded_data_marital_status2

Compute the magnitude to get most significant variables

# Train a linear SVM model with the final_data dataset

train.setg <- train.set
train.setg <- apply(train.setg, 2, as.numeric)


final.svm.linear.calc <- svm(Fixed_Ownership ~ ., data = train.setg, kernel = "linear")

# Get the coefficients for the linear SVM model
svm.coef <- coef(final.svm.linear.calc)

# Compute the magnitude of the coefficients
svm.coef.abs <- abs(svm.coef)

# Extract the top 3 input variables with the largest coefficient magnitudes
top.vars <- names(sort(svm.coef.abs, decreasing = TRUE)[1:8])
top.vars

Produces svm plot for INCTOT and Age

# split data into train and test sets
train.setg1 <- as.data.frame(train.setg)

training <- sample(1:nrow(train.setg1), size = 400)
train.plot <- train.setg1[training, ]
test.plot <- train.setg1[-training, ]

# create radial kernel SVM model
svm_rad_plot <- svm(Fixed_Ownership ~ INCTOT + AGE, data = train.plot, kernel = "radial")

# plot SVM decision boundary
plot(svm_rad_plot, train.plot, INCTOT~AGE,  
     main = 'SVM Radial Kernel Plot', 
     xlab = 'INCTOT', ylab = 'AGE',
     width = 10, height = 10)

# create grid of values for prediction
ind_income_grid <- seq(min(train.setg1$INCTOT), max(train.setg1$INCTOT), length.out = 100)
age_income_grid <- seq(min(train.setg1$AGE), max(train.setg1$AGE), length.out = 100)
grid_data <- expand.grid(INCTOT = ind_income_grid, AGE = age_income_grid)
predicted_data <- predict(svm_rad_plot, newdata = grid_data)

# combine prediction with grid data
plot_data <- cbind(grid_data, prediction = predicted_data)

# create SVM plot
# create SVM plot
ggplot(data = plot_data, aes(x = INCTOT, y = AGE)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = prediction)) +
  scale_color_gradient(low = "red", high = "blue") +
  stat_contour_filled(aes(z = as.numeric(prediction)), alpha = 0.2) +
  labs(title = "SVM Radial Kernel Plot", x = "Individual Income", y = "Age") +
  theme_bw() + guides(fill = FALSE) #Remove Legends
